Notes on Subset Provenance
--------------------------
- **Benchathon** subset: original tasks and human grades collected by the
  BenGER team. CC BY 4.0 applies directly.

- **ZJS** subset: case texts (`Aufgabe`, `Musterlösung`) are derived from
  *Zeitschrift für das Juristische Studium* (www.zjs-online.com). For each
  case, the dataset records the IP-clearance status given by the original
  author. Cases whose authors have not approved redistribution are replaced
  with a placeholder URL pointing back to the ZJS search interface
  (https://www.zjs-online.com/index.php?sektion=3). The non-redacted
  metadata (title, author, citation) is reproduced under the academic
  citation conventions of the underlying journal; the redacted full-text
  cases are released under CC BY 4.0 only for cases the author cleared.
  Author-supplied requests for anonymisation are honoured by replacing the
  `Autoren` field with the literal string "Anonymisiert".

- **Grundprinzipien** subset: original multiple-choice items composed by
  the BenGER team. CC BY 4.0 applies directly.

